<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-747-280  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 747 280.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Sept 11 1989 v3 n37 p20(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CALS document standard under review: document type definitionspecs included to ensure consistency. (Computer-Aided Acquisitionand Logistics Support)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Smithmidford, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Pentagon and National Institute of Standards and Technologyissued a new military standard updating the electronic documentformat under the Computer- Aided Acquisition and Logistics Support(CALS) program.andP;  CALS is an initiative to convert weaponsdocumentation from paper to electronic media, thus enablinginformation sharing via a common set of standards and formats.andO;The new version allows for Standard Generalized Markup Language(SGML) styles called document type definitions (DTDs).andP;  Eventuallythere will be a central registry of DTDs to ensure consistency ofdocumentation, although some weapons will still need uniquedocumentation styles.andP;  Industry and government officials arereviewing a draft of the document; vendors expect that the draftwill be further refined before approval is granted.andP;  A finalversion of the draft is due by the end of 1989.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Department of DefenseUnited States. National Institute of Standards and TechnologyStandardsMilitaryGovernment AgencyDocument Delivery.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>